Our correspondent Yan Guowen and Wu Yueming contributed to this report from Beijing and Guangzhou

In the face mask has become the most urgent material situation, since February, the founder of Jianke Su Zhan has repeatedly reported the real name Jianke network and CEO  sales of fake face masks.

"The company's minority shareholder, Xie Fangmin, used the company's APP and Jianke.com  platform to sell the three-piece mask at a price ten times higher than the market. So far, she has received complaints from many victims across the country, " Su reported

On March 2, the Huangpu District Market Supervision Bureau of Guangzhou replied to a reporter from the China business daily that it had checked Jianke twice. In the first case, no price gouging was found. In the second case, a case has been filed against the suspected sale of fake and inferior masks. The case is under investigation.

During the outbreak, why would the founder of a well-known Online Pharmacy report that his company Sold three-no-fake masks? On March 1, Su Zhan explained to the reporter that his evidence also comes from the complaint of Netizens to Jianke. com. "because the appearance of fake medicine and mask touches the basic bottom line of life and work. This is something I can not stand, " Su said.

According to Su, as the founder of Jianke, has been decentralized for many years, the full management of Jianke by Xie Fangmin. After several rounds of financing, the network built a VIE structure, has been valued at hundreds of millions of dollars, and had planned to go public in the United States. In July 2019, however, the two sides clashed over the company's seal.

However, Ms Xie denied what Su had reported. On March 2, Xie Fangmin told reporters that the masks sold on Jianke's platform were in compliance with the law and that many complaints were false. "Su Zhan is not a major shareholder of the company, but a minority shareholder, who currently has less than 30 percent of the voting power and was removed by a collective decision of the company's board last year, " Xie said

However, Ms Xie did not respond to a request for comment that the company had been placed under investigation by the Guangzhou Huangpu District Market Supervision Authority.

The mask that was "switched" 

The reporter noticed that in a network platform for complaints, during the outbreak of a lot of complaints for the sale of masks Jianke network.

On March 2, a consumer in Fujian Province, Xiao Wang, told reporters that his original purchase was a surgical mask for medical use, but he did not think that businesses would replace it with a disposable blue non-woven mask without notice. Screenshots of the orders provided by the company show that the manufacturer of the mask was also replaced by Guangdong Hongrui Medical Equipment Co. , Ltd. .

Guangzhou Huangpu District Market Supervision Bureau has sent staff to the company to investigate the situation is true.

On March 2, the reporter logged on to the Jianke APP to inquire about the related product information, but did not search the company to produce the mask. It is puzzling, however, that other products have been pulled from shelves despite the fact that they are out of stock and are marked as out of stock on the page.

The masks bought by Wang were not the only ones to be switched. Has Been placed under investigation

On March 2, the Huangpu District Market Supervision and Administration Bureau of Guangzhou City provided reporters with a "statement on the verification of complaints against "Guangzhou Yunyi Hui Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. " for allegedly illegal business operations. Regarding the reported "price gouging" , on February 1,2020, the bureau sent law enforcement officers to the accused to check on the spot, and so far there has been no "price gouging" by the accused, and in accordance with the procedure to return the relevant examination of the complainant.

Since February, the bureau has received reports of suspected illegal activities such as the sale of three-no masks. On 14,15 and 21 February, the bureau organised three visits by law enforcement officers to the scene of the complainants for investigation and evidence collection. After investigation, in accordance with the law, the parties involved in the sale of counterfeit and inferior mask acts on file. The case is currently under investigation.

On March 2, Guangzhou Yunyihui Pharmaceutical Co. , Ltd. , which is currently owned by Jianke, issued a statement in response to the reported incident, "selling masks and three-nil products at 10 times the market price is a deliberate act of Su Zhan and others to fabricate facts, gossip and seriously undermine the normal operation of our company. The relevant law enforcement departments of the government had come to our company for investigation after receiving the complaint earlier. Our company has cooperated with the law enforcement departments and submitted relevant certification materials. The law enforcement departments have made it clear that our company's business conduct is lawful and lawful."

On March 2, Xie Fangmin said in an interview that the mask is 100% no problem. "By comparing the masks we sell from the 1st to the 6th day of the 1st Lunar Month with those on other platforms that haven't changed prices, we have completely changed the concept. Now the market supervision bureau checked, there is no problem at all. There is no question of price, there is no question of three, there is no question of false propaganda, and the conclusion is all there. So there's nothing wrong with the mask."

Notably, neither the statement nor Ms Xie responded to a request for comment that the company had been placed under investigation by Huangpu District's market regulator.

In response to the problems arising from Jianke's website, Zhao Yunfan, a lawyer with Guangdong Mingcan law firm, told reporters on March 2 that from the perspective of civil compensation, if Jianke's website is found to be fraudulent, then the consumer may request the Jianke net according to "the consumer rights and Interests Protection Law" stipulation refunds 1 to 3. From the perspective of administrative liability, violations of the product quality law will face fines, confiscation of illegal income penalties, the serious circumstances may be revoked Business license.

From the perspective of criminal liability, the sale of three-no masks or fake masks may be suspected of constituting the concurrence of the crimes of producing and selling fake or inferior products, the crimes of selling commodities with fake trademarks, and the crimes of producing and selling medical equipment that does not meet the standards, the Penal Code provides for a choice of felonies.

The website for the filing is called Yunyihui medicine official website. The filing and review date for approval is September 27,2019.
